history.content:
Depends on what you're looking for. Probably more than a few years ago, the answer would be undoubtedly CS162, but nowadays it's common for a lot of successful programmers to not need much systems knowledge. But if you want only a single answer, I would still say CS162.

If you're only looking at web/mobile development, I would take CS186 or CS161, in that order of priority. If you're unable to get any internships, maybe take CS169.

If you're looking for research or any other type of software engineering that's not web/mobile, I would take CS162.

To be the most well-rounded, however, you'll probably need at least CS162 and CS186, not just one out of that list.
